Yes. Once you have **DTE, DMSP, DUC, and DTI**, I would actually move away from using only the aggregate DEE score.

One of the likely reviewer comments is:

> "Which dimension of the digital entrepreneurship ecosystem is actually affected?"

Using the four pillars solves that.

From what you've described, I'd redesign the paper as follows.

# Core idea

The paper is no longer:

> Digital dependency and DEE.

The paper becomes:

> How digital trade network structures shape different dimensions of digital entrepreneurship ecosystems.

That is a stronger and more nuanced contribution.

